Enhance your games with modular terrain designed for easy integration of LEDs, servo motors, and smoke effects—no soldering or programming required! Components can be installed in minutes, with a hollowed base and wiring channels ready for your custom setup.

Note: This is a DIY project for hobbyists; you'll need to source and assemble your own electronics. STL files only—no physical parts included. Some learning and experimentation may be needed, making it a fun skill-building experience.

✅ Support-Free Printing – Flawless prints without supports.
✅ Expertly Designed – No clean-up, clips, or glue required.
✅ FDM Optimised – Tested for printers like Ender 3, A1 Mini, and Bambu P1S.

Free 3d printable terrain! This is a promotional model for our latest terrain Kickstarter, The Zectonium Prison Mines.
https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/saucermenstudios/zectonium-prison-mines?ref=6lj6ke

The Zectonium Prison Mines is a vast collection of 3D printable terrain that gives you the creative freedom to build immersive industrial landscapes and brutal, off-world mining facilities.

With a core set of 110+ models, this huge collection of terrain features an impressive level of detail and modularity. Sections are interchangeable, so the theme and layout is chosen by you! The additional 200+ stretch goal models expand the options by introducing more building components, mining infrastructure, minerals, vehicles, alien ruins, drilling machinery and much, much more.
